    "name": "Monte Carlo global sensitivity analysis for hemolysis index prediction",
    "description": "A 2048-sample Monte Carlo global sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices) was performed varying six dominant input parameters: blood viscosity (±8%), pump rotational speed (±3%), inlet flow rate (±5%), RBC fragility scalar (±15%), power-law hemolysis model exponent (±10%), and wall roughness height (±20%). Hemolysis index was identified as most sensitive to the RBC fragility scalar (first-order Sobol index S1=0.41) and power-law exponent (S1=0.29), with rotational speed contributing S1=0.18; remaining factors contributed less than 0.05 each. Total-order indices confirmed negligible higher-order interactions beyond the top three factors.",
    "method": "Sobol quasi-random Monte Carlo",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "RBC fragility scalar",
      "power-law hemolysis exponent",
      "rotational speed"
