  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou2/decision/accepted-mrl5",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at MRL 5. Eleven factors achieved requiredLevel; two factors (Model form, Model inputs) required Gradation 5 and achieved Gradation 5 through Bayesian model averaging and experimentally-derived PDFs respectively. Monte Carlo UQ (2048 samples) confirms 95th-percentile NIH remains 38% below clinical threshold of 0.1 g/100L across all operating points. Sobol sensitivity analysis identifies dominant uncertainty contributors (RBC fragility scalar, power-law exponent, rotational speed) and confirms no unexpected sensitivity pathways. Validation against FDA benchmark on identical geometry with full COU envelope coverage provides high confidence in predictive fidelity. Mean NIH prediction error 8.3% within ±15% acceptance band with no systematic bias. Discretization error bounded at 4.1% GCI. All software quality, verification, and use-error controls at Gradation 4 or above. The totality of structured evidence supports acceptance of the CFD model for predicting absolute hemolysis levels in the Class III VAD COU at MRL 5.",
